  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7_27",
    "text": "Fig. 5. Detection of CTB in cocultures of V. cholerae and epithelial cells. (A) Fluorescence images of Caco-2 monolayers postincubation (5 h) either with a 1:100 dilution of V. cholerae (from an initial ODs0o = 1.0, a 0.01 dilution) or with medium only (no V. cholerae). Cells were washed and probed with BEGs before imaging (40× magnification). (B) Bound CTB was quantified following lysis of bound BEGs in experiments using either 1:100 and 1:1000 dilutions of V. cholerae or medium only as a control (no VC). Cocultures ran for the time indicated, and the amount of CB bound was calculated from a standard curve on Caco-2 cells. Error bars were calculated as a percentage for each sample from the fluorescence measurements of triplicate experiments.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5213178273697338,
      0.4418604653296365,
      0.9476744125677955,
      0.5479651161757245
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7",
    "order": 41
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7_2",
    "text": "Fig. 4. Estimation of CTB bound per well. (A) Western blots of known amounts of CTB (ng) were scanned and analyzed for blot density (pixels). Blot density versus CTB amounts were plotted to obtain a logarithmic correlation (inset). (B) The amounts of CTB bound to cells were then calculated from Western blots (using the equation from the panel A inset) and compared with fluorescence data from gangliosome analysis of epithelia exposed to the same amounts of CTB. This equation was thereafter used to estimate the amount of CTB bound to epithelia based on gangliosome fluorescence (Fig. 5). Data points represent averages of at least triplicate experiments. Error bars in panel A represent 1 standard deviation of triplicate experiments. RFU, relative fluorescence units.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.069767450350061,
      0.44618055538033635,
      0.4961240408845658,
      0.5523313490049936
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7",
    "order": 42
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7_43",
    "text": "specifically for V. cholerae growth and CT production, and it contains a higher salt concentration than does AKI medium [61]. After washing away the V. cholerae, we treated the Caco-2 cells with gangliosomes (BEGs) and viewed them under a fluorescence microscope (Fig. 5A) before lysing and measuring fluorescence in a microtiter plate reader (Fig. 5B.). We also estimated the amount of CTB bound to each well by Western blot and correlated that estimate with the fluorescence for that well.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5213178369346767,
      0.5711805556478995,
      0.9476744111273387,
      0.6744186044569747
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.ab.2008.05.027.pdf_7",
    "order": 43
  },
